<paragraph id="8BF6070DFF92F75BFF38FCAD26C2FCE7" blockId="9.[189,467,831,863]" box="[189,467,831,863]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<heading id="D0BEB061FF92F75BFF38FCAD26C2FCE7" bold="true" box="[189,467,831,863]" fontSize="13" level="1" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF92F75BFF38FCAD26C2FCE7" bold="true" box="[189,467,831,863]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF92F75BFF38FCAD27E4FCE7" bold="true" box="[189,245,831,862]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">The</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C497C8EFF92F75BFF78FCD22665FCE6" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1905" box="[253,372,832,863]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteata">balteata</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF92F75BFEFBFCD226C2FCE7" bold="true" box="[382,467,832,862]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">group</emphasis>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF6070DFF92F75BFF38FCE423BFFA84" blockId="9.[189,1399,886,1341]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
The four known members of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C497C8EFF92F75BFDC3FCE425B7FC29" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1905" box="[582,678,886,912]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteata">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF92F75BFDC3FCE425B7FC29" box="[582,678,886,912]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">balteata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group possess two distinctive broad, deep rosy bands on the forewing; a pattern that is not found in other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C497C8EFF92F75BFCE3FC0B24D7FC0A" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1858" box="[870,966,921,947]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF92F75BFCE3FC0B24D7FC0A" box="[870,966,921,947]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Callipia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The male valvae are round-shaped and do not possess the spine-like processes on the ventral margin that are present in all other groups of 
<taxonomicName id="4C497C8EFF92F75BFF58FC73262CFC42" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1858" box="[221,317,993,1019]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF92F75BFF58FC73262CFC42" box="[221,317,993,1019]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Callipia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The uncus is pointed. The aedeagi are bulkier than in other 
<taxonomicName id="4C497C8EFF92F75BFB8CFC732378FC42" authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1858" box="[1033,1129,993,1019]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF92F75BFB8CFC732378FC42" box="[1033,1129,993,1019]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Callipia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the vesica is long and has a small series of cornuti. The species are restricted to high elevations in the wet eastern Peruvian and Bolivian Andes (observed: 
<quantity id="4CB1AAE8FF92F75BFDB3FBBA25CFFBFA" box="[566,734,1064,1091]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.716" metricValueMax="3.45" metricValueMin="1.982" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="m" value="2716.0" valueMax="3450.0" valueMin="1982.0">
<date id="FFF721CDFF92F75BFDB3FBBA257EFBFA" box="[566,623,1064,1091]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1982">1982</date>
–3450 m
</quantity>
). All are represented by a single or very few specimens in museum collections only. Surprisingly, the 
<taxonomicName id="4C497C8EFF92F75BFD5AFBDE242EFBDF" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1905" box="[735,831,1100,1126]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteata">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF92F75BFD5AFBDE242EFBDF" box="[735,831,1100,1126]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">balteata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group consists of relatively many species, with small, but clear morphological differences besides supporting molecular information. One species was collected in 
<collectingRegion id="498DC9EFFF92F75BFE0DFB0626E3FB17" box="[392,498,1172,1198]" country="Peru" name="Huanuco" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Huánuco</collectingRegion>
Province, Central 
<collectingCountry id="F35E479DFF92F75BFD51FB06241BFB17" box="[724,778,1172,1198]" name="Peru" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C497C8EFF92F75BFC98FB06249EFB17" authority="Brehm, 2018" authorityName="Brehm" authorityYear="2018" box="[797,911,1172,1198]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamasi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF92F75BFC98FB06249EFB17" box="[797,911,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. lamasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20E6664FF92F75BFC1CFB0624E8FB17" box="[921,1017,1172,1198]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), ca 
<quantity id="4CB1AAE8FF92F75BFBB6FB06239FFB17" box="[1075,1166,1172,1199]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="km" value="850.0">850 km</quantity>
separated from the collection site of 
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF92F75BFE03FB2A2513FB6B" box="[390,514,1208,1234]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. fiedleri</emphasis>
sp. nov. (
<collectingCountry id="F35E479DFF92F75BFDEFFB2A25B5FB6B" box="[618,676,1208,1234]" name="Peru" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="498DC9EFFF92F75BFD2AFB2A25E9FB6B" box="[687,760,1208,1234]" country="Peru" name="Cusco" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Cusco</collectingRegion>
Province), separated by ca 
<quantity id="4CB1AAE8FF92F75BFBBFFB252380FB68" box="[1082,1169,1207,1234]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="km" value="250.0">250 km</quantity>
from the collection site of 
<taxonomicName id="4C497C8EFF92F75BFE95FB4E2682FB4C" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1905" box="[272,403,1243,1270]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteata">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF92F75BFE95FB4E2682FB4C" box="[272,403,1243,1270]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. balteata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Peru, 
<collectingRegion id="498DC9EFFF92F75BFE69FB4E2539FB4F" box="[492,552,1244,1270]" country="Peru" name="Puno" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Puno</collectingRegion>
Province) and separated by another ca 
<quantity id="4CB1AAE8FF92F75BFB85FB49234BFB4C" box="[1024,1114,1243,1270]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="km" value="250.0">250 km</quantity>
from the collection site of 
<taxonomicName id="4C497C8EFF92F75BFF5AFA92265DFAA0" authority="Brehm, 2018" authorityName="Brehm" authorityYear="2018" box="[223,332,1279,1306]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jakobi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF92F75BFF5AFA92265DFAA0" box="[223,332,1279,1306]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">C. jakobi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20E6664FF92F75BFED0FA9226A3FAA3" box="[341,434,1280,1306]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(western Bolivia). The 
<taxonomicName id="4C497C8EFF92F75BFD55FB6D2421FAA0" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1905" box="[720,816,1279,1305]" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Callipia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balteata">
<emphasis id="B93DDB1FFF92F75BFD55FB6D2421FAA0" box="[720,816,1279,1305]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">balteata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group represents an example of an Andean high elevation clade with a large degree of local endemism. The females are still unknown.
</paragraph>
